WHO   — THE D20 — a techne sphere — the art
WHAT  — A d20 is an icosahedron: twenty triangular faces, twelve vertices, thirty edges — one of the five Platonic solids the Greeks held to be the perfect shapes of reality. It is also the totem of the tabletop dice-roller and a staple of geometric tattoo flash. This sphere makes it the seal of TECHNĒ: a rotating ink-wireframe ringed in sacred geometry.
